sub_title: Helping women with a 9 to 5 launch their online coaching businesses from scratch in 60 days
summary:
👋🏾Hi everyone! 

My name is Trudy and I'm a senior client success specialist and founder of the platform called Digital Dreamers Hub where I'm an online business coach.

💡Fun fact about me, in November 2016, I graduated with a master's degree in International Fashion Marketing thinking I would be pursuing a career in fashion. I could envision it! Little did I know that my career would be going in a totally different direction. 

🛫In January 2017, I hopped on a plane to Dublin, Ireland to pursue a career in tech, with ZERO experience in the tech space. I got referred by a friend and since I was a new grad I thought, let's goooo!

So what happened next?
Little did I know that pivoting in the tech space would open so many opportunities for me.

🎯With the experience I gained working for Google, I started my freelance business helping small to medium-sized businesses with their online advertising presence. It was one of the best and most liberating experiences in my career.

🚀It opened doors to working for a major online recruitment tech company which I'm currently working for right now and recently got promoted to senior.

❓With all of these experiences acquired throughout the years, there has been a passion to pass on this knowledge. To be frank, I've had this passion for a long time but wasn't sure about the "what" and "how". 

✨November 2021, I had this AHA - moment to create a platform called the Digital Dreamers Hub where I share my knowledge on how people can get clarity on how to easily start an online service-based business in 2023. An online business that always leads with purpose. This comes from the mission that women shouldn't be choosing between time and money. They can have both in every life-defining moment.

📨Here are some resources you can start using;

🚀Check out the podcast episodes: https://spoti.fi/3xY2WF9
🚀Follow the Instagram page: @digitaldreamershub
🚀Send me an email: hello@digitaldreamershub.com
🚀Book a free call: https://calendly.com/digitaldreamershub/20mins

projects.title: Nationale Dag Van De Communicatie
projects.description:
During the Nationale Dag Van De Communicatie (National Day Of Communication) in Amsterdam, I teamed up with freelance blogger Jonathan Zegbe to present the topic of online marketing and blogging to students of the University of Amsterdam. 
During our presentation, we discussed what blogging is, how to start one, basic SEO strategies to gain more clicks/views and how to get in touch with PR agencies and brands.

profile_positions.description:
Digital Dreamers Hub is a community for women that want to move away from the societal status quo and tap into their dreams of starting their first online businesses. We want to make sure that every woman can have a seat at the table even if it means that she has to bring her own chair. 

At digital dreamers hub, we believe that every woman should be able to make any career decisions that will make them happy without it impacting the longevity of their wealth. 

So if you're ready to start your very first online business with confidence, ease and a lot of clarity, you're at the right place!

profile_positions.description:
Danso Digital is a young digital marketing agency with an expertise in Google Adwords. Danso Digital is your partner in digital marketing to help you implement effective online marketing strategies to achieve the best ROI for your company.

As the main focus is to target Ghanaian start-ups and enterprises, a new way of acquiring prospects has been implemented. Search Engine Advertising is fairly new in Ghana and not frequently considered nor implemented in a company's marketing strategies. In Ghana, the use of the internet and the usage of mobile phones is increasing year by year. The challenging part here and our mission is to make businesses understand why considering and implementing such a strategy can make a difference in the way they do business. And why they should re-evaluate their advertising channels and tap into the ''new'' way of advertising and finding its target audience effectively online.
profile_positions.title: Founder

profile_positions.description:
The first 5 months within Accenture, I was working as an Onboarding Specialist for Google Adwords. I was responsible for the incoming calls within the Benelux market. The focus was mainly on small to medium-size businesses. The queries that I had to solve were very diverse. Each case was unique and there were different ways and strategies to solve the cases that were coming in. The queries that I was responsible for were mainly around conversion strategies, billing issues, Google Analytics, Google Merchant Center and Google My Business. After each query I was also responsible for optimizing the Google Adwords campaigns of the customer i order for it to perform better.

From May 2017, I was offered a new position within the Google Adwords project. I started my role as an Account Executive for the Benelux market. Every week, I received 50 new leads (Google Adwords customers) that I was responsible for. My main responsibility was to call as many customers to analyze their current Google Adwords strategy and the company's short/ long term goals. With all this information it was my responsibility to optimize the customer's Adwords campaign as effectively and efficiently as possible in order for the customer to generate a higher ROI.
profile_positions.title: Account Strategist Google Adwords

profile_positions.description: My role as a Customer Service Representative at the well-known iconic British department store Liberty was fast-paced. My main role was to be quick with problem-solving when customers had queries regarding delivery, Liberty loyalty program and product enquiries. This role required good communication skills in both writing and speaking, good product knowledge and experience in premium customer service.
profile_positions.title: Customer Service Representative (Temp.)

profile_positions.description: I started working as a sales consultant at the London based brand Molton Brown in October 2015. This was ideal because of the flexibility in terms of hours in order for me to combine it with my masters studies. As a sales consultant I'm responsible for offering premium service to each and every customer we steps into the store. Besides that, it's very important to inform the customers about the product categories, product fragrances and most important of all understand what the customers are looking for. Finally, it's important to build a strong customer relationship and this done by offering the customers to be on the mailing list.
profile_positions.title: Sales Consultant

profile_positions.description: I've been working in a close and versatile group at the Swarovski boutique. As a sales consultant, you continuously challenge yourself to provide premium customer experience and to tell a story/history with the luxury products at Swarovski. Besides providing premium customer service, we put an emphasis on maintaining customer relationships as well by introducing our core products and providing  the supplementary services in a professional and unique way.
profile_positions.title: Sales Consultant

profile_positions.description: I did my 5 month internship at the vibrant and international company Coty Benelux. During the 5 months of internship I was a marketing assistant within the division Coty Prestige where I got the work with luxury fragrances such as Marc Jacobs, Chloe, Balenciaga, Calvin Klein, Roberto Cavalli, Davidoff and philosophy. The main tasks were organizing and creating factsheet for the monthly meetings with the account managers, sending visuals aids to our clients, send off incentives in form of fragrances, brainstorming and coming up with marketing campaigns, preparing sales meetings, taking responsibility regarding merchandising tasks and maintaining customer relationship with the company's key clients.
